programme.title: Inside Superyachts
programme.desc: On this first episode of Inside Superyachts we meet with the Godfather of Superyacht builders ? Feadship Yachts. Established in 1849, this Dutch shipyard is not only the number one in the industry but also the most famous of all superyacht builders, having created masterpieces for the likes of Steve Jobs.From the Netherlands we take a trip down to the ultra-discreet Principality of Monaco, host of the greatest yacht Pascoe Tenders open their doors to us to have a look inside these space-aged, hyperluxurious tenders.

programme.title: Salon Nautique Paris
programme.desc: Welcome to the 2019 edition of the Salon Nautique de Paris. This boat show has an international scale and hundreds of nautical enthusiasts come inside to find out the latest trends in superyachts, rental services or sport equipment. Be part of the best moments of this Boat Show and discover the latest innovations in the marine world on the 2019 season of the Salon Nautique Paris.

programme.title: Transat Jacques Vabre
programme.desc: The 'Transat Jacques Vabre' returns on Nautical Channel. Follow the multihulls and monohulls from the start at Le Havre to their arrival at Itajai in Brazil. Inspired by the historic coffee trade routes between Europe and the New World, this race takes its competitors on a non-stop 5,450 nautical mile course from France to Brazil. For a shot at victory sailors will have to remain vigilant in this extreme test of endu.

programme.title: Maxiboat TV Show
programme.desc: The best show for maxiboats lovers has docked. programme.title: The Survivalist
programme.desc: A year and a half after the fall of civilization due to a viral outbreak, a former FBI agent is forced to protect a young woman immune to the disease from a dangerous gang leader hunting her.

programme.title: The DUFF
programme.desc: A high-school senior (Mae Whitman) sets out to reinvent herself and revolutionize the student body's social order after learning that a judgmental classmate has given her an embarrassing nickname. [(18748)]

programme.title: The Inspection
programme.desc: Based on the incredible true story of a gay Black man with few options who joins the Marines to prove himself to his estranged mother and triumph in a system that cast him aside, unexpectedly finding strength and camaraderie in this new community.

programme.title: Catch Me if You Can
programme.desc: An FBI agent (Tom Hanks) pursues Frank Abagnale Jr., a con man (Leonardo DiCaprio) who assumes various identities and commits forgery.

programme.title: Tammy's Always Dying
programme.desc: A woman comes to a crossroad when her perpetually troubled mother becomes terminally ill.

programme.title: Dangerous Game: The Legacy Murders
programme.desc: A reunion at a remote mansion takes a lethal turn when family members are forced to play a deadly survival game where only one will make it out alive.

programme.title: Club Cumming Presents a Queer Comedy Extravaganza!
programme.desc: Tony Award winner Alan Cumming hosts a cabaret-style gathering featuring seven up-and-coming queer comics that represent not only the diversity of the queer spectrum, but also of comedy styling -- from stand-up to characters to musical performances.

programme.title: Megalodon Rising
programme.desc: An armada of modern warships proves no match for a megalodon: a giant shark thought to be extinct.

programme.title: Hitsville: The Making of Motown
programme.desc: Motown Records becomes the most successful label of all time after its formation in 1958 Detroit amid racial tension and the burgeoning civil rights movement.

programme.title: The Florida Project
programme.desc: Set in the shadow of the most magical place on Earth, 6-year-old Moonee and her two best friends forge their own adventures, while Moonee's struggling mom and a kindhearted motel manager protect the kids from the harsh reality that surrounds them.

programme.title: The Loneliest Boy in the World
programme.desc: A satire and a celebration of family values, the imagery of horror films, suburban life, the American Dream, and the ultimate taboo: death.

programme.title: The Last Airbender
programme.desc: A being (Noah Ringer) with the ability to manipulate the four elements joins forces with a waterbender (Nicola Peltz) and her brother to restore balance to their war-torn world.

programme.title: Wifelike
programme.desc: When artificial human Meredith gets assigned as a companion to grieving widower William, it's designed to behave like his late wife. However, it soon begins to question reality as memories of a past life begin to resurface.

programme.title: Margaux
programme.desc: As seniors celebrate their final college days at a smart house, its highly advanced AI system, Margaux, begins to take on a deadly presence. A weekend of partying soon turns into a dystopian nightmare as they realize Margaux plans to eliminate them.

programme.title: Good Time
programme.desc: A bank robber stops at nothing to free his brother from prison, launching himself into a nightlong odyssey through New York's dark and dangerous criminal underworld.

programme.title: The Bigfoot Trap
programme.desc: A journalist's life changes forever when he finds himself locked inside a bigfoot trap by an insane sasquatch hunter. [(18748)]

programme.title: Fire Island
programme.desc: The perfect summer vacation quickly spirals out of control for a group of friends on the infamous, picturesque party getaway of Fire Island as they find themselves caught in a web of sex, lies and cold-blooded murder.

programme.title: Crawlspace
programme.desc: After witnessing a brutal murder in a cabin, a man hides in a crawlspace while the killers scour the property for a hidden fortune. As they draw nearer, he must decide if the crawlspace will be his tomb or the battleground in his fight for survival.

programme.title: Margaux
programme.desc: As seniors celebrate their final college days at a smart house, its highly advanced AI system, Margaux, begins to take on a deadly presence. A weekend of partying soon turns into a dystopian nightmare as they realize Margaux plans to eliminate them.

programme.title: Paradise Hills
programme.desc: Young women must band together to escape from a seemingly idyllic island that holds a sinister secret.

programme.title: Songs My Brothers Taught Me
programme.desc: Johnny and his sister Jashuan live with their single mother on a reservation. When their absentee father dies, Johnny feels compelled to strike out for a new life in LA, but fears leaving his sister behind.

programme.title: The Lovers
programme.desc: A man and his wife, each embroiled in an extramarital affair, are sent reeling when they suddenly fall for the least likely person imaginable -- each other.

programme.title: Cut Bank
programme.desc: Things go from bad to worse when a murder witness (Liam Hemsworth) in small-town Montana tries to leverage the crime into a get-rich-quick scheme.

programme.title: Inbetween Girl
programme.desc: After her parents' sudden divorce, teen artist Angie Chen turns to secret hookups with popular jock Liam. As Angie contends with her parents' divorce and her secret fling with Liam, she comes to discover what she wants -- and who she wants to be.

programme.title: Disgraced
programme.desc: An examination of the events surrounding the 2003 murder of Baylor University men's basketball star Patrick Dennehy.

programme.title: Post Mortem
programme.desc: Shortly after World War I and in the middle of the Spanish flu, a post-mortem photographer and a girl confront supernatural happenings.

programme.title: Our Ghosts
programme.desc: Hiding in the attic of his former apartment, a widowed and jobless father tries to scare the new tenant so he can live there once again.

programme.title: Montana Story
programme.desc: Two estranged siblings return home to the sprawling ranch they once knew and loved in order to care for their ailing father.

programme.title: The Whale
programme.desc: A reclusive English teacher, living alone in the wake of a tragedy, attempts to reconnect with his teenage daughter for one last chance at redemption.

programme.title: Deadlocked: How America Shaped the Supreme Court
